title: How to Stop a Baby Crying using the 'Dr Hamilton' technique. It works!! :)
description:

‚Äì  Doesn't royalty-free music mean I can use it for free?

'Royalty-free' music is not the same as 'free music'. Unfortunately, this is a common misconception on the internet, and especially here on YouTube.

Welcome to Minibus - Nursery Rhymes & Kids Songs! Minibus is a channel with popular and educational nursery rhymes and songs for babies and children. Subscribe for free for more videos each week : https://www.youtube.com/minibusandfriends/?sub_confirmation=1

Learning and educating children in a fun way is always more effective. This is why we created the universe of Minibus and Friends. Indeed, with the help of nursery rhymes cartoons for kids depicting endearing characters, we offer educational nursery rhymes for babies and children, to learn the alphabet, numbers, colors, healthy habits, animals and all kinds of subjects.

Our rhymes are simple to understand and repetitive enough for the child to easily assimilate words.
And our videos are accompanied by subtitles so that the child can follow by reading the lyrics and sing along.

Don't hesitate to subscribe for free to our YouTube channel to never miss anything from our future publications : https://www.youtube.com/minibusandfriends

See you soon on Minibus and Friends!

title: Baby White Noise for Sleep & Colic Relief | No Ads While Sleeping!
description:
Sometimes it can be hard for your little one to get sleep at night. That struggle is amplified by the fact that babies can't communicate their needs, often leaving parents attempting every solution to get them to settle. If you find yourself in a similar situation with your baby, we may have the perfect solution for you! Baby white noise can be a powerful tool every parent should have on their utility belt! The consistent sleep sound creates a calming atmosphere that can help ease your babies colic. Additionally, baby white noise can help cover up outside sounds that keep your baby up at night. Not to mention, this sleep white noise sounds just like what babies heard in the womb, bringing a sense of familiarity with all that comfort! Millions of parents rely on white noise to sleep when they put their precious one to sleep. Next time your child is struggling to feel relaxed, you should give it a try too! You may never have another bedtime without it! 

While playing white noise for babies, it‚Äôs important to keep tabs on the volume, because any white noise machine, smartphone, or computer can put out levels that are too loud for your child. It's recommended to play the sound at least a few feet from where your infant is sleeping and to keep the volume no louder than the sound of a soft shower.

Parents can download an app to turn their smartphone into a sound level meter. One good, free, option is the sound level meter app created by the U.S. National Institutes for Occupational Safety and Health (NIOSH) available on the app store as the NIOSH SLM app.
